<br>
In terms of style, this is a real winner.  Okay, fire elemental casting ice spells might not make too much sense.  But it looks cool.  If nothing else, these guys qualify as a *fun* spell.  (Fun spells are a double-edged sword for Verant, of course; people are always complaining that their fun spells are &quot;useless&quot;, or else complaining that they don't have an fun spells.)<br>
<br>
Ice comet itself - who cares?  It's a great spell in the early 50's when you need an ice nuke.  But it quickly becomes obsolete as you go up in levels.  By level 63 if you still consider Ice Comet something sacred and special, you need to update your spell book.<br>
<br>
Usefullness - Somebody above said that this pet is useless for xp groups or raids.  I question that.  Luclin mobs, for instance, have *huge* melee damage mitigation; a spell-casting pet might do better against them.  Similarly, aren't there raid mobs who are 100% melee-immune?  The mage pet advantage is supposed to be diversity - different pets for different occasions.  This is just a continuation of that.<br>
<br>
NPC Wizard AI - NPC wizards are stupid.  I'm *much* more affraid of an NPC wizard who's out of mana.  The spells are a nuisance; the melee is deadly. <p>Bayler - Marauder/Deceiver - Xev<br>
